				<td colspan="2" height="100%" valign="top"><span class="postbody"><FONT SIZE=+1>Guild News - March 31, 2005</FONT>
<br />

<br />
<FONT SIZE=-1 COLOR=#444444><I>"The characteristic of heroism is its persistency. All men have wandering impulses, fits, and starts of generosity. But when you have chosen your part, abide by it, and do not weakly try to reconcile yourself with the world. The heroic cannot be the common, nor the common the heroic."</I></FONT>
<br />
 - Ralph Waldo Emerson
<br />

<br />
A lot has happened since the last guild news update. We have a new site banner (visible in the forums...the front page hasn't been updated yet), a <A HREF="http://www.scienceofwar.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=9">new recruitment process</a>, <A HREF="http://www.scienceofwar.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=11865">several new officers</A>, and a <A HREF="http://www.scienceofwar.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=12134">big game patch</a>. Intrepid professors of the SoW <I>School of Advanced Tactical Studies</I> have ventured deep into Dire Maul and have emerged with bags of loot and stories aplenty. Meanwhile, the remainder of the guild has been leveling up rapidly. It looks like a large portion of the guild will reach 60 by the early half of April, way ahead of schedule. Larger guild raids aren't far away.
<br />

<br />
<B>New Members</B>
<br />

<br />
The guild has adopted changes to the application review process, based on our experience with handling apps so far. Applicants are now given a membership interview by guild officers after two weeks of initiate status. Based on the results of the interview, the feedback of the guild membership, and the involvement of the initiate we then decide to boot the player, give them another two weeks, or promote them to full member. This has helped us move through applications at a faster pace.
<br />

<br />
Since the last news update, we have promoted <strike>four</strike> five players to full member status:
<br />
<UL><LI>Razorr - <FONT COLOR=#777777>Hunter</FONT>
<br />
<LI>Najira - <FONT COLOR=#777777>Priest</FONT>
<br />
<LI>Figleaf - <FONT COLOR=#77777>Druid</FONT>
<br />
<LI>Junckey - <FONT COLOR=#77777>Rogue</FONT>
<br />
<LI>Ireg - <FONT COLOR=#777777>Warrior</FONT></UL>These new members have all demonstrated adaptability, intelligence, and skill. Congratulations and welcome to the ranks!
<br />

<br />
<B>New Officers</B>
<br />

<br />
Science of War is proud to announce the promotion of two members to the officership:
<br />
<UL><LI>Phobeus - <FONT COLOR=#7777FF>Recruitment Officer</FONT>
<br />
<LI>Softwinna - <FONT COLOR=#7777FF>Recruitment Officer</FONT></UL>Professors Phobeus and Softwinna have been assigned the task of recruiting new applicants, receiving applications, and monitoring initiates. So far their results have been fantastic and there are a lot of new names in our applicant channel.
<br />

<br />
Being an officer in SoW is a bit different from your standard guild. We don't grant officer status as a reward for long service or to favorite members. Each officer fills a specific role defined by a job description and a set of monthly requirements. Any member can volunteer for an office, but they are responsible for meeting certain goals and quality standards to retain the position. Officers are then "paid" for their duties (usually through a periodic DKP bonus). This system forms an officer corps that shares the work involved in building and running a top tier guild.
<br />

<br />
<B>Membership Requirements</B>
<br />

<br />
We are now under phase 2 of the <A HREF="http://www.scienceofwar.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=12021">Guild Level Calendar</A>. Applications will be accepted for players of any level, but initiates must be at least level <b>35</b> in order to qualify for full membership. There's still plenty of time for applicants from other servers to create a character on <b>Azjol-Nerub</B> and play with us!
<br />

<br />
<B>One Ugly Chick</B>
<br />

<br />
<I>Update: Images turned to links.</I>
<br />
<A HREF="http://www.scienceofwar.net/flatline/images/news/theradras.jpg">Theradras farting.</A>
<br />
<A HREF="http://www.scienceofwar.net/flatline/images/news/dead_theradras.jpg">Theradras dead.</a>
<br />

<br />
Maraudon loot is on the menu. Click the image for a nice shot of the fallen corpse of the #1 bitch. Does that thing even qualify as female? Guest appearance by the Ninja Turtles on this run, where we managed to shell out an ass kicking on four inner Maraudon bosses for more loot than you can fit in Kraang's Technodrome. Or something.</span><br /><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
